    <item>
      <title>Re: Empty fields when submit form, and no error...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/powercontent/forum/general/empty_fields_when_submit_form_and_no_error_message/re_empty_fields_when_submit_form_and_no_error</link>
      <description>Hi,&#13;
&#13;
It appears suhosin extension limits varname lenght to 64 characters by default. (post key name)&#13;
&#13;
So, such post variables was not submitted.&#13;
&#13;
I change 2 lines in my suhosin.ini :&#13;
&lt;code&gt;suhosin.post.max_name_length = 256&#13;
suhosin.request.max_varname_length = 256&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
And it works !&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Simon Boyer)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/powercontent/forum/general/empty_fields_when_submit_form_and_no_error_message/re_empty_fields_when_submit_form_and_no_error</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2011 09:46:03 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
